com.camerontec.catalys.server.configuration.model

Class SessionState

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.configuration.model.SessionState

  • public class SessionState
extends Object
    This class is representing a session containing all attributes relevant to determine the state. It is used in operations to simply browse the current state of session as well as advice the server to change the state of sessions. In the latter case only the attributes 'active', 'blocked' and 'locked' will actually have an effect. 'connected' and 'reloadable' only have informational purposed and cannot be influenced via the below operations.
    Since:
    Catalys 2.0
    Author:
    CameronTec - Jonas Weinrich
    See Also:
    ApplicationConfigurationMXBeanSpecific.makeSessionsReloadable(java.util.Set), ApplicationConfigurationMXBeanSpecific.sessionStateSummary(), ApplicationConfigurationMXBeanSpecific.restoreSessionStates(java.util.Map)
